  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want the onboarding flow to use similar patterns both mobile and desktop so I am not confused. \r\n\r\nAs developer / QA, I want to introduce latest UI changes in desktop so its design is pretty much similar to the mobile app and does not look outdated\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Update Opt Metrics screen for Status Desktop \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nStatus Desktop Opt Metrics screen looks similar to mobile (copy and design). Images used are high quality (resolution) so the app does not look blurry. Use dynamic pictures where possible so the layout is not broken in full-screen and collapsed window\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/40022393-8895ee7c-57d0-11e8-9f3d-f6e81c4899d3.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nOld style is used, images are poor quality\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/28752642/40022421-a5da50a4-57d0-11e8-8e0e-0891f3bba318.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status Desktop\r\n- Create Account\r\n- Restore Account\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: have no idea, something we got last week (May 7-11)\r\n* Operating System: macOS",
